The party has now given the ANC until the end of March to finish the process of reincorporating Matatiele into KZN or face losing the metros of Ekurhuleni and Rustenburg. JOHANNESBURG The African Independent Congress (AIC) has described its meeting with the African National Congress (ANC) on Tuesday as positive, saying that the governing party has guaranteed that the process to incorporate Matatiele back into KwaZulu-Natal will be sped up.The AIC, which was formed in protest against the demarcation of Matatiele into the Eastern Cape, went into coalition with the ANC in Ekurhuleni after last year s local government elections.Its key demand was Matatiele s incorporation back into KwaZulu-Natal.However, its meetings with the party have dragged on since August last year.The party has now given the ANC until the end of March to finish the process or face losing the metros of Ekurhuleni and Rustenburg.AIC president Mandla Galo says: The secretary general of the ANC and the secretary general of the AIC must draft the memorandum of understanding, with time frames. Jeff Radebe, as the leader of the ANC team, will kick start the consultation. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)